      <head>Wilhelm Hausenstein</head>
      <div>

        <p>German author, editor, and politician; German ambassador to France after 1945.</p>

        <p>Hausenstein served on the staff of the <ref cRef="entity-002552"><title level="j"
              >MÃ¼nchener Neueste Nachrichten</title></ref> until 1933, when the Munich police force
          had him dismissed from the editorial board. Thereafter, he worked on the <ref
            cRef="entity-002537"><title level="j">Frankfurter Zeitung</title></ref> from 1934 until
          its enforced closure in 1943. Hausenstein was married to a Belgian Jewish interpreter,
          Marguerite Kohn.</p>
